Quote:  The <i>kotaha</i> was a carved stick with a short length of cord [27] attached to one end. <i>ibid.</i> 273 The <i>kotaha</i> was described by Smith (81, p.73) as a handle with a whip-lash which was wound round a spear stuck in the ground.
